==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fuzz
<hw>Fuzz</hw> <pr>(f⟦ucr⟧z)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To make
drunk.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wood.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fuzz</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fuzz
<hw>Fuzz</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Prov. E. <ets>fuzzy</ets> that
ravels (of silk or cotton), D. <ets>voos</ets> spongy, fungous, G.
<ets>faser</ets> filament. E. <ets>feaze</ets> to untwist.]</ety>
<def>Fine, light particles or fibers; loose, volatile matter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fuzz ball</b></col>, <cd>a kind of fungus or mushroom,
which, when pressed, bursts and scatters a fine dust; a
puffball.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fuzz</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Fuzz
<hw>Fuzz</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To fly off in minute
particles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fuzzle</ent>⟦br⟧
